-- China May Start Implementing Property Tax in 2 to 3 Years, Daily Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-22T23:01:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/china-may-start-implementing-property-tax-in-2-to-3-years-daily-reports.html

          
          
             China may start implementation of a
property tax in two to three years, the China Daily reported
today, citing an unidentified person at the Ministry of Finance.  
 The tax would be tested in some cities before being
introduced on a nationwide basis, the newspaper reported.  
          
          


  


        